cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use the Open Agent Protocol in your research, please cite it using the metadata in this file."
title: "Open Agent Protocol"
abstract: >-
  The Open Agent Protocol is a vendor neutral standard for how autonomous
  agents discover, invoke, pay for, govern, and audit the tools and services
  they use. It defines a single conformance surface that unifies identity,
  capability description, structured invocation, monetization, multi agent
  coordination, confidentiality enforcement, and tamper evident auditing.
type: software
version: "1.0.0-pwd"
date-released: 2026-05-01
license:
  - Apache-2.0
  - CC-BY-4.0
url: "https://openagentprotocol.eu"
repository-code: "https://github.com/openagentprotocol-OAP/oap-spec"
repository-artifact: "https://github.com/openagentprotocol-OAP/oap-spec/releases"
keywords:
  - autonomous agents
  - multi agent systems
  - agent protocol
  - interoperability
  - agent economy
  - decentralized identity
  - verifiable credentials
  - agent query language
  - conformance
  - policy engine
  - tamper evident audit
